[Student "S"]
{NORTH has an opening hand, 14 points and five \Ss. But WEST beat him to the punch, 
so he overcalls 1\S. 

SOUTH also has 14 points, she doesn't care too much for \Ss, but she has an 
excellent stopper in \Hs. 
She jumps to 2NT, inviting NORTH to bid game.

Since NORTH has several points more than he might have had, and no 6-card \S suit to rebid, 
he happily bids 3NT.}

